{
  "stem": "1132.1",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "There was a Hungarian Nazi party that was created, which was called the White Arrowheads, who were getting increasingly vocal and increasingly giving a lot of trouble to Jews.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Now again, being in-- having been in the capital, we have had noticeably fewer problems than those who were in the country and in smaller cities.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "I have recollections of the Germans marching into Budapest, and I have those recollections on March 19th, 1944.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "I remember the famous German military step as they walked in, and I remember watching it from a window and being very scared, obviously, not knowing what was going to happen.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "As part of the laws against the Jews, one of the first ones was, as I indicated, that Jewish professionals could no longer practice.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "So that took my father's practice away completely.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Then Jews were forced to move into designated buildings.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "This was not really the real ghetto.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "There was a ghetto part as well, but we were not in-- called a ghetto.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "We were a designated building which was reserved for people with the yellow star.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "Now, we were among those, obviously-- all the Jews, as in other parts of Europe, had to wear the yellow star.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And I have the original yellow stars, which I hope we will take pictures of.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "It just so happens that the apartment house that I was brought up in was designated as one of these specific Jewish houses, so that we had other families move in with us.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "We-- the four of us-- my family was a nuclear family of four-- remained in that apartment, and we had two other families moving in.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "Now, we were lucky because one of-- both of those families were people we did know.",
      "word_count": 16
    }
  ],
